The restaurant closed for good last month.

00:00:52.615 --> 00:00:53.949
You'll be safe here.

00:01:01.332 --> 00:01:02.583
Pink?

00:01:06.796 --> 00:01:08.506
You chose these on purpose, didn't you?

00:01:08.589 --> 00:01:10.132
I got a car under someone else's name.

00:01:11.092 --> 00:01:12.176
The phone is a bonus.

00:01:14.970 --> 00:01:16.097
This is cash.

00:01:16.180 --> 00:01:17.973
It has
a 60-month interest-free installment plan.

00:01:19.100 --> 00:01:21.310
Don't run away with the money.
You're a judge.

00:01:25.231 --> 00:01:26.816
I was so proud to have
a judge as a friend!

00:01:28.192 --> 00:01:29.735
Sin-jin, that bastard!

00:01:33.614 --> 00:01:36.117
- Calm down.
- I'm just so sad!

00:01:36.200 --> 00:01:37.201
Still, calm down.

00:01:43.708 --> 00:01:45.000
You're bleeding from your neck

00:01:45.626 --> 00:01:46.627
and coughing.

00:02:07.982 --> 00:02:09.442
I can't let you

00:02:10.526 --> 00:02:12.611
kill me twice.

00:02:17.491 --> 00:02:18.868
Right, Sin-jin?

00:02:40.264 --> 00:02:41.348
We meet again.

00:02:42.767 --> 00:02:44.560
I hear you were very worried about me.

00:02:53.360 --> 00:02:54.612
What happened?

00:02:56.155 --> 00:02:58.908
Sin-jin tried to overthrow Suojae.

00:02:58.991 --> 00:03:00.493
That was how Gyo-hun got killed.

00:03:01.535 --> 00:03:05.039
And you're returning to Seoul
because I said I needed you.

00:03:05.498 --> 00:03:07.333
I asked Mr. Baek to move you back.

00:03:08.292 --> 00:03:09.460
That's great.

00:03:10.002 --> 00:03:12.838
Yong-hyeon will be so happy
to see me back in Seoul.

00:03:15.341 --> 00:03:16.342
Let's get to work.

00:03:22.473 --> 00:03:24.725
I thought you'd be gone for good.

00:03:27.812 --> 00:03:29.396
I'm impressed that you made it back.

00:03:32.775 --> 00:03:34.193
It's just a witness questioning.

00:03:34.276 --> 00:03:36.529
How nice is it that I get to say hi?
I love that.

00:03:39.865 --> 00:03:40.866
Gosh

00:03:40.950 --> 00:03:42.701
I didn't know young people these days

00:03:42.785 --> 00:03:45.579
had the nerve to haul an old man in
just to say hello.

00:03:47.081 --> 00:03:49.291
What a tough world it is.

00:03:50.751 --> 00:03:52.586
The world has gone crazy!

00:04:06.308 --> 00:04:07.601
Hello.

00:04:08.060 --> 00:04:09.854
We're closed for the day.

00:04:15.359 --> 00:04:16.610
Hello.

00:04:18.362 --> 00:04:20.614
I'm Mr. Lee's colleague.

00:04:35.921 --> 00:04:38.048
His surgery went well

00:04:38.132 --> 00:04:39.300
and he's doing fine.

00:04:39.675 --> 00:04:40.759
Really?

00:04:41.260 --> 00:04:42.428
- Yes.
- So...

00:04:42.511 --> 00:04:43.888
You're sure

00:04:43.971 --> 00:04:45.389
our Han-young is safe?

00:04:45.472 --> 00:04:46.473
Yeah.

00:04:46.932 --> 00:04:48.642
So, don't worry at all.

00:04:48.726 --> 00:04:50.102
Don't skip your meals

00:04:50.185 --> 00:04:51.854
and stay healthy

00:04:51.937 --> 00:04:53.772
until Mr. Lee returns.

00:04:54.607 --> 00:04:55.691
Do you understand?

00:04:58.569 --> 00:05:00.112
But by the way

00:05:00.654 --> 00:05:02.072
did Han-young...

00:05:06.201 --> 00:05:07.745
really do that?

00:05:10.539 --> 00:05:11.874
Of course not.

00:05:11.957 --> 00:05:13.208
He's just being accused.

00:05:14.501 --> 00:05:15.502
My goodness.

00:05:15.961 --> 00:05:17.171
My Han-young...

00:05:17.546 --> 00:05:18.881
Who did that?

00:05:19.214 --> 00:05:20.215
Who's the jerk

00:05:20.299 --> 00:05:22.176
accusing my Han-young of murder?

00:05:27.264 --> 00:05:28.265
"Father

00:05:28.849 --> 00:05:29.850
and mother

00:05:30.059 --> 00:05:32.311
I'll find the one who accused me

00:05:32.394 --> 00:05:33.771
prove my innocence

00:05:34.563 --> 00:05:36.231
and return proudly."

00:05:41.570 --> 00:05:43.614
Had Mr. Lee been here

00:05:43.697 --> 00:05:47.493
he probably would've said that.

00:05:50.871 --> 00:05:52.039
Thank you.

00:05:52.122 --> 00:05:53.832
- Don't worry.
- Okay.

00:06:02.007 --> 00:06:03.676
That'll be 3,500 won.

00:06:15.521 --> 00:06:16.897
Don't tell me you believe

00:06:16.981 --> 00:06:18.399
what you hear on the news

00:06:18.816 --> 00:06:20.025
about Han-young.

00:06:20.901 --> 00:06:22.403
Who would believe that nonsense?

00:06:28.158 --> 00:06:29.618
Don't cry.

00:06:29.702 --> 00:06:31.954
Han-young can tell when you're crying.

00:06:32.705 --> 00:06:35.165
Focus on your studies all the more.

00:06:36.041 --> 00:06:37.042
And here.

00:06:37.126 --> 00:06:38.419
Don't forget your treats.

00:06:41.046 --> 00:06:42.047
Okay.

00:06:52.016 --> 00:06:54.393
CEO YU SEON-CHEOL

00:06:55.019 --> 00:06:56.895
You called me?

00:06:58.397 --> 00:07:01.150
Why didn't you just go home? You're drunk.

00:07:01.233 --> 00:07:02.359
You told me to come here.

00:07:29.553 --> 00:07:30.554
Go to a school abroad.

00:07:40.355 --> 00:07:42.649
You brought the evidence for Han-young.

00:07:42.733 --> 00:07:44.651
You might get involved
in an unnecessary mess.

00:08:09.718 --> 00:08:10.719
I...

00:08:12.930 --> 00:08:14.515
didn't like living here, anyway.

00:08:23.524 --> 00:08:24.650
Don't tell me...

00:08:26.819 --> 00:08:28.570
I'll leave.

00:08:34.493 --> 00:08:36.870
I'll leave, okay?

00:08:47.422 --> 00:08:49.341
I'll go abroad to study.

00:08:53.720 --> 00:08:55.931
Sin-jin was

00:08:56.014 --> 00:08:57.432
always close by.

00:08:58.392 --> 00:09:02.563
After all, who hasn't gone to court
from political or business circles?

00:09:05.524 --> 00:09:08.777
Prosecutors and attorneys can talk
all they want

00:09:09.236 --> 00:09:10.320
but at the end of the day

00:09:10.529 --> 00:09:11.613
the judge gets the final say.

00:09:15.576 --> 00:09:16.702
Who is it this time?

00:09:18.120 --> 00:09:19.121
Hmm?

00:09:28.964 --> 00:09:31.175
You were the first name he mentioned.

00:09:36.680 --> 00:09:37.973
Of course.

00:09:41.018 --> 00:09:43.145
I must've disappointed the old man
big time.

00:10:03.415 --> 00:10:04.917
You look like you're going to war.

00:10:06.084 --> 00:10:07.294
Hurry.

00:10:10.047 --> 00:10:11.131
From the Executive Branch

00:10:11.215 --> 00:10:13.258
to Hanyang's development
and National Pension investments

00:10:13.342 --> 00:10:15.219
Suojae had a grip on everything.

00:10:15.302 --> 00:10:17.471
What was going on in Suojae?

00:10:17.888 --> 00:10:18.889
So, it's...

00:10:19.640 --> 00:10:20.682
Mr. Lee!

00:10:21.183 --> 00:10:22.726
How are you? Are you okay?

00:10:23.268 --> 00:10:24.269
Your neck.

00:10:24.478 --> 00:10:25.479
I'm fine.

00:10:26.021 --> 00:10:27.481
Yeah, that's not the focus.

00:10:27.564 --> 00:10:29.733
I'm being accused of murder!
Any questions about that?

00:10:29.816 --> 00:10:32.069
- Who'd believe that?
- I'd sooner believe in ghosts!

00:10:32.152 --> 00:10:33.237
You know, I spent the day

00:10:33.320 --> 00:10:36.031
visiting your parents and Na-yeong
before coming here.

00:10:36.114 --> 00:10:37.449
I told everyone

00:10:37.532 --> 00:10:39.952
you were just being framed
and told them to relax.

00:10:40.035 --> 00:10:41.578
Don't disappoint me like that.

00:10:41.662 --> 00:10:42.704
Thank you.

00:10:43.622 --> 00:10:44.623
That's right.

00:10:44.706 --> 00:10:46.041
Sin-jin

00:10:46.124 --> 00:10:47.501
overthrew Suojae.

00:10:49.628 --> 00:10:50.837
First

00:10:50.921 --> 00:10:52.506
we need to clear your name.

00:10:53.298 --> 00:10:55.050
Someone definitely took your blood

00:10:55.133 --> 00:10:56.718
and smeared it on the corpse

00:10:56.802 --> 00:10:58.220
and all over the crime scene.

00:10:59.304 --> 00:11:01.598
Whoever did it,
Sin-jin must've made them do it.

00:11:02.266 --> 00:11:04.726
We have to find Sin-jin first, then.

00:11:04.810 --> 00:11:07.020
He has no family or relatives.

00:11:07.104 --> 00:11:08.522
Where could he be hiding?

00:11:09.439 --> 00:11:11.483
Find me before the police do.

00:11:12.192 --> 00:11:14.111
That's the least you can do

00:11:14.194 --> 00:11:15.696
to be cleared of the accusation.

00:11:18.031 --> 00:11:19.574
Sin-jin wants me

00:11:19.658 --> 00:11:21.285
to find him.

00:11:23.829 --> 00:11:25.455
Yes, Han Jeong-hun speaking.

00:11:27.374 --> 00:11:29.376
Not only will I hide Mr. Jang's record

00:11:29.459 --> 00:11:31.420
of illegal political funds
in the last election

00:11:33.046 --> 00:11:36.091
but I'll also bury any proof of his bribes
in the National Convention.

00:11:37.134 --> 00:11:38.135
Okay.

00:11:38.385 --> 00:11:39.469
I understand.

00:12:08.373 --> 00:12:09.958
Everyone is here.

00:12:10.042 --> 00:12:11.126
You can talk.

00:12:14.338 --> 00:12:17.007
All of you are
in the Presidentâ€™s hands and mine.

00:12:18.842 --> 00:12:22.387
I just sent you the files
of all your illegal deeds.

00:12:28.393 --> 00:12:30.979
But if you help me return

00:12:31.438 --> 00:12:33.899
the world will never see those files.

00:12:34.608 --> 00:12:35.734
Mr. President

00:12:36.068 --> 00:12:37.694
is confessing all our secrets

00:12:37.778 --> 00:12:38.862
to the prosecution.

00:12:45.994 --> 00:12:48.705
If Mr. President goes down,
he'll take the fall for it all.

00:12:49.289 --> 00:12:50.916
I'll make him.

00:13:11.353 --> 00:13:13.188
Nothing will change from before.

00:13:14.689 --> 00:13:16.441
I'll replace Mr. President

00:13:16.525 --> 00:13:18.026
and work with you all

00:13:19.403 --> 00:13:21.405
to lead our nation.

00:13:40.590 --> 00:13:43.218
That's impressive for someone
who's on the run.

00:13:45.387 --> 00:13:47.889
Sin-jin knows
all the Suojae members' dirty secrets.

00:13:47.973 --> 00:13:48.974
He'll try to use them

00:13:49.057 --> 00:13:50.892
to go back to where he was.

00:13:50.976 --> 00:13:53.478
Sin-jin is a murderer. He killed Gyo-hun.

00:13:53.562 --> 00:13:54.855
Whether he accuses someone

00:13:54.938 --> 00:13:56.481
or kills more people to silence them

00:13:57.274 --> 00:13:59.067
he believes he can do anything he wants.

00:13:59.151 --> 00:14:00.277
That's Sin-jin for you.

00:14:01.403 --> 00:14:02.946
We can't let him have it his way.

00:14:03.363 --> 00:14:05.073
You came sooner than I expected.

00:14:05.157 --> 00:14:06.450
How have you been?

00:14:07.159 --> 00:14:08.160
Well

00:14:08.243 --> 00:14:09.494
it's not too bad.

00:14:17.377 --> 00:14:19.296
This has all the files
on the Suojae members.

00:14:19.379 --> 00:14:20.380
It contains

00:14:20.464 --> 00:14:22.215
their second phone numbers.

00:14:27.637 --> 00:14:29.556
But I've been very busy lately.

00:14:30.223 --> 00:14:31.933
With the serial cabbage theft

00:14:32.017 --> 00:14:33.685
and Kkamang, the breeding goat.

00:14:34.102 --> 00:14:35.604
Serial cabbage theft

00:14:35.687 --> 00:14:37.022
and Kkamang, the breeding goat?

00:14:37.230 --> 00:14:38.231
You can add this

00:14:38.315 --> 00:14:40.609
to your list, then. It's nothing big.

00:14:43.153 --> 00:14:44.988
You realize this is the southernmost city?

00:14:45.614 --> 00:14:47.073
If I get pushed out any farther

00:14:47.157 --> 00:14:49.159
I might meet the Little Mermaid
and her family.

00:14:49.743 --> 00:14:51.244
There will be a feud in Suojae soon

00:14:51.328 --> 00:14:52.829
and they'll all be on their own.

00:14:53.622 --> 00:14:54.706
So, first

00:14:54.789 --> 00:14:57.876
let's start by tracking
the Suojae members' second phones.

00:14:59.044 --> 00:15:00.795
I have to track every single one, right?

00:15:00.879 --> 00:15:02.297
LIST OF SECOND PHONE NUMBERS
OF THE SUOJAE MEMBERS

00:15:02.380 --> 00:15:03.465
Hey, Mr. Kim.

00:15:04.174 --> 00:15:06.635
You know the case of cabbage theft?

00:15:06.718 --> 00:15:07.886
I've done some research

00:15:07.969 --> 00:15:09.679
and it's a really big deal.

00:15:10.222 --> 00:15:13.266
We'll need to ask phone service providers
for location tracking.

00:15:13.642 --> 00:15:16.895
I put my job on the line
to track those phones.

00:15:31.493 --> 00:15:32.494
We need to find

00:15:32.577 --> 00:15:34.329
Nam-yong's flash drive that Sin-jin has.

00:15:34.829 --> 00:15:37.290
That's the only way
to wipe everyone out at once.

00:15:37.666 --> 00:15:39.417
Aren't we in trouble, even if we find it?

00:15:40.877 --> 00:15:42.712
Let's think about that after we find it.

00:15:55.267 --> 00:15:59.354
Should we side with Sin-jin or not?

00:15:59.437 --> 00:16:01.273
We probably should.

00:16:06.570 --> 00:16:09.656
Won't the President-elect
try to strike us?

00:16:09.739 --> 00:16:12.033
He'll try to achieve something big
in the beginning.

00:16:12.117 --> 00:16:14.119
You say that

00:16:15.078 --> 00:16:17.414
as if the President-elect has never run
in elections.

00:16:17.497 --> 00:16:19.040
I'm sure

00:16:19.124 --> 00:16:21.376
Sin-jin, that snake, doesn't just have

00:16:21.459 --> 00:16:23.920
our lives at his fingertips.

00:16:24.004 --> 00:16:25.005
Oh!

00:16:25.088 --> 00:16:26.548
Illegal campaign funds.

00:16:42.772 --> 00:16:43.982
Did you request for support?

00:16:45.108 --> 00:16:47.193
Are you crazy? What, to get you arrested?

00:17:26.232 --> 00:17:28.026
Roll the window down and raise both hands.

00:17:34.240 --> 00:17:35.241
Hello.

00:17:40.038 --> 00:17:41.164
I'm on duty.

00:18:03.645 --> 00:18:04.646
Yes.

00:18:04.729 --> 00:18:06.481
That's a record
of politicians and law firms

00:18:06.564 --> 00:18:08.108
bribing judges in court.

00:18:11.611 --> 00:18:13.571
Han-young knows about the restaurant

00:18:13.655 --> 00:18:15.615
so the police may barge in anytime.

00:18:17.826 --> 00:18:18.910
Keep all of it safe

00:18:18.993 --> 00:18:20.578
until I return.

00:18:24.666 --> 00:18:25.667
Okay.

00:18:25.750 --> 00:18:26.835
Will do, Mr. Kang.

00:18:59.159 --> 00:19:00.410
That's impressive.

00:19:02.287 --> 00:19:05.123
I still have enough power to visit prison.

00:19:05.206 --> 00:19:06.207
So?

00:19:06.875 --> 00:19:08.918
I need your slush fund account.

00:19:09.002 --> 00:19:11.588
And what do I get in return?

00:19:12.130 --> 00:19:14.424
I'll bring you back to Suojae.

00:19:17.552 --> 00:19:19.888
Didn't you try to kill me last time?

00:19:19.971 --> 00:19:21.306
Tables have turned.

00:19:27.312 --> 00:19:28.521
It's too late.

00:19:29.314 --> 00:19:32.108
I've already told
a little too much to the prosecution.

00:19:32.192 --> 00:19:33.777
Including things about you.

00:19:35.153 --> 00:19:36.488
Once I provide the proof

00:19:36.571 --> 00:19:37.947
all of you will get arrested.

00:19:39.949 --> 00:19:41.284
You still have a chance.

00:19:41.701 --> 00:19:43.787
Testimonies coerced by the prosecution

00:19:43.870 --> 00:19:45.663
can be backtracked easily.

00:19:46.623 --> 00:19:47.624
No.

00:19:48.041 --> 00:19:49.626
The world has changed.

00:19:50.084 --> 00:19:53.546
I have all the files Nam-yong collected
from the Election Commission.

00:19:53.630 --> 00:19:56.049
The record of illicit political funds
of assemblymen

00:19:56.132 --> 00:19:57.884
and the past and present Presidents

00:19:57.967 --> 00:19:59.469
that Nam-yong collected
in the National Election Commission.

00:20:00.178 --> 00:20:02.263
Of course, you're in it, too.

00:20:02.472 --> 00:20:03.765
I already know that.

00:20:13.483 --> 00:20:14.484
Of course.

00:20:15.735 --> 00:20:17.320
The new President-elect

00:20:17.403 --> 00:20:20.114
wore the badge in the last election.

00:20:20.740 --> 00:20:21.825
I'm sure

00:20:21.908 --> 00:20:23.576
he didn't just use documented funds

00:20:23.660 --> 00:20:25.620
to win in that election.

00:20:25.703 --> 00:20:28.331
If you snitch on the illegal funds
of the new President-elect

00:20:28.873 --> 00:20:31.543
he won't even have the power
to form a new Cabinet.

00:20:33.044 --> 00:20:35.672
They'll be eliminated at the hearing,
the Prime Minister included.

00:20:35.755 --> 00:20:38.716
A lame-duck government from the start...

00:20:42.637 --> 00:20:44.097
The new President-elect

00:20:44.180 --> 00:20:45.473
wouldn't appreciate that.

00:20:52.564 --> 00:20:54.691
How about an account

00:20:55.108 --> 00:20:56.150
with 30 billion won?

00:21:15.920 --> 00:21:18.339
At the end of the day,
only money and power persevere.

00:21:34.439 --> 00:21:35.523
He just got out.

00:21:37.317 --> 00:21:38.484
Okay.

00:21:40.361 --> 00:21:42.363
Get Se-hee out of the country fast.

00:21:57.754 --> 00:21:58.755
Thanks.

00:22:05.595 --> 00:22:06.596
Hey!

00:22:07.263 --> 00:22:09.057
Sin-jin just dropped by.

00:22:09.974 --> 00:22:12.560
He mentioned some files from Nam-yong.

00:22:12.936 --> 00:22:15.688
He has dirt
on the new President-elect, too.

00:22:16.439 --> 00:22:17.649
Sin-jin.

00:22:18.608 --> 00:22:20.401
Sin-jin is probably trying to return

00:22:20.485 --> 00:22:22.111
by blackmailing the President-elect.

00:22:22.195 --> 00:22:24.322
I know, but he offered

00:22:24.405 --> 00:22:26.407
to get me back in Suojae.

00:22:26.491 --> 00:22:28.159
I know he's lying, but I like the idea.

00:22:29.410 --> 00:22:30.495
So

00:22:30.828 --> 00:22:32.956
I gave him access to a hidden account

00:22:33.039 --> 00:22:36.250
that gets 10% of the monthly donations
from Seojin Happiness Foundation.

00:22:47.845 --> 00:22:49.055
What a disgusting laugh.

00:22:50.223 --> 00:22:51.724
They're all unbelievable.

00:22:53.351 --> 00:22:54.435
This is great.

00:22:55.228 --> 00:22:57.605
We can definitely arrest Sin-jin
with this.

